<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - ELECTRONIC
        ENGINE CONTROLS - CATERPILLAR 3406B -1991 - WELDING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="0">
        <title>WELDING</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>Disconnect both the positive (+) and negative (-) battery cables from the battery before welding
                    on the vehicle. Attach the welder ground cable as close as possible to the part being welded. Do not
                    connect the ground cable of the welder to the cooling plate or control module(s). To protect the
                    control module(s) computer circuits, it is mandatory to remove all connectors going to the control
                    module(s).
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
